INTEL GPU DRIVERS FOR LINUX - https://dgpu-docs.intel.com/index.html
Intel® software for general purpose GPU capabilities – Intel Opencl, Intel Level Zero and Media SDK

sudo zypper addrepo -r https://repositories.intel.com/graphics/sles/15sp3/intel-graphics.repo

sudo zypper update
sudo zypper install intel-opencl intel-media-driver intel-level-zero-gpu level-zero intel-gpu-tools libdrm_intel1 libvulkan_intel xf86-video-intel libdrm2 libdrm-tools libmfx1 intel-igc-cm intel-metrics-discovery intel-metrics-discovery intel-ocloc libigc-tools libigc1 libigdfcl1 libmfx-utils libmfxgen1 libvpl-tools libvpl2

Add user to render and video group:
sudo gpasswd -a ${USER} video
sudo gpasswd -a ${USER} render

KNOWN ISSUES:
Unable to find OpenCL*

If you are installing libOpenCL1 from Tumbleweed, the OpenCL ICD loader recently changed the location for vendor files from /etc/OpenCL to /usr/share/OpenCL. The intel-opencl package above currently installs to /etc/OpenCL. To work with the updated vendor location, you need to copy the vendor file to /user/share/OpenCL after installing the intel-opencl package:

if [[ ! -d /usr/share/OpenCL/vendors ]]; then
  sudo mkdir -p /usr/share/OpenCL/vendors
fi
sudo cp /etc/OpenCL/vendors/intel.icd /usr/share/OpenCL/vendors/intel.icd

Sources: https://dgpu-docs.intel.com/installation-guides/suse/suse-15sp3.html
